graph TD
    A[Load Dataset] --> B[Extract Claims]
    B --> C[Generate Questions]
    C --> D[Retrieve Evidence via Google Search]
    D --> E[Identify Stance of Evidence]
    E --> F[Determine Verdict]
    F --> G[Visualize Results]

    %% Details for each step
    B --> B1[Step 1: Extract Claims]
    B1 --> B2[Uses LLM to extract up to 3 claims per text.]
    B2 --> B3[Example: From "The economy grew by 5% last year," extract "The economy grew by 5%."]

    C --> C1[Step 2: Generate Questions]
    C1 --> C2[Uses LLM to generate 3 fact-checking questions per claim.]
    C2 --> C3[Example: For "The economy grew by 5%," generate "What was the GDP growth last year?"]

    D --> D1[Step 3: Retrieve Evidence via Google Search]
    D1 --> D2[Uses Google API to retrieve top 3 search results for each question.]
    D2 --> D3[Example: Search for "What was the GDP growth last year?" and retrieve snippets.]

    E --> E1[Step 4: Identify Stance of Evidence]
    E1 --> E2[Uses LLM to classify evidence as "Completely Supports," "Refute," etc.]
    E2 --> E3[Example: Evidence like "The GDP grew by 5.1% last year" is classified as "Completely Supports."]

    F --> F1[Step 5: Determine Verdict]
    F1 --> F2[Aggregates stances to calculate a score and determine the final verdict.]
    F2 --> F3[Example: If most evidence refutes the claim, the verdict is "Spreading Misinformation."]

    G --> G1[Step 6: Visualize Results]
    G1 --> G2[Visualizes stance counts and verdict distributions for each party.]
    G2 --> G3[Example: Create bar plots comparing stances and verdicts across parties.]

    %% Styling for processes
    style B1 fill:#cce5ff,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px
    style C1 fill:#cce5ff,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px
    style D1 fill:#cce5ff,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px
    style E1 fill:#cce5ff,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px
    style F1 fill:#cce5ff,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px
    style G1 fill:#cce5ff,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px


